<Class name="CM_JRWTrackedItems" id="419c397d-0e3d-4cbe-a727-e748cc9e71a9">
    <superclass name="CM_JRWTransient"/>
    <transient/>
    <persistentAllowed/>
    <sharedTransientAllowed/>
    <subclassPersistentAllowed/>
    <subclassSharedTransientAllowed/>
    <subclassTransientAllowed/>
    <transientAllowed/>
    <text>create attributes 'qryXXXX' to pass to the report writer as the query parameters to appear
on the report itself. In this way, your JRW root collection 
(which will have one instance of this class in it) can have 
any number of collections, references or attributes within it.</text>
